OL,3,CReport finds 'failings' in case of
OL,4,Cbanned driver left free to kill
OL,6,FIt said Kelk had breached at least
OL,7,Fseven licence conditions he had been
OL,8,Fgiven following previous offences and
OL,9,Fhad "continued to drive illegally and
OL,10,Fwas not deterred by the consequences".
OL,12,FThe report said practitioners
OL,13,F"minimised the risks" he posed and
OL,14,F"action needed to be taken sooner to
OL,15,Fconsider recall (to prison)".
OL,17,FThe Ministry of Justice apologised
OL,18,F"unreservedly" for the "significant
OL,19,Fpractice failings" in Kelk's case.
